node.text:
“Without Brooklyn there would be no Flipp.” Flipp Dinero stops by FCNY to perform live for Flight Club Fridays. The Brooklyn rapper explains how his trials & tribulations have molded him, further contributing to his rounded understanding of music. Flipp developed his eclectic taste in music from being open to diverse sounds growing up, ultimately forming the melodic identity which led him to earning his first multi-platinum certification from the RIAA. To conclude the evening, Flipp gave us an intimate performance of his hit record "Leave Me Alone." Producer/Editor - Derek Putlak
Director of Photography - Marshall Douglis
Camera Operator - Taylor Washington

node.title: Flight Club Fridays - Flipp Dinero Performs "Leave Me Alone" Live @ FCNY

node.text:
“Your feet represent you and how you’re feeling at the current time.” Flipp Dinero stops by FCNY to perform live for Flight Club Fridays. The Brooklyn rapper describes his hometown as “very creative” and “emotion-packed” while checking out FCNY’s grail case – mentioning his infatuation with Jordans and how he always dreamed of having the Air Jordan 6 Retro NRG “Green Suede Gatorade” sneakers while on tour. Flipp then performed his hit songs "Feelin Like" and "I Do" to an intimate crowd. 
Producer/Editor - Derek Putlak 
Director of Photography - Marshall Douglis 
Camera Operator - Taylor Washington

node.title: Flight Club Fridays - Flipp Dinero Performs "Feeling Like" Live @ FCNY

node.text: Hear the 2019 NBA rookie class’ take on this year’s MVP, which star they’re most excited to faceoff with, the first jersey they have ever owned and more. Presented by Flight Club & The Players’ Tribune.

node.title: Flight Club x TPT: 2019 NBA Rookies talk MVP race, first jersey, and more

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 12, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: A three-way collaboration featuring two of Jordan Brand’s most influential cohorts, the Fragment Design x Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro High emerges in a white tumbled leather base with Military Blue overlays along the toe box, collar and outsole. The sneaker takes color-blocking elements from Hiroshi Fujiwara’s 2014 AJ1 collab, while Travis Scott’s imprints appear in an inverted Swoosh and hidden heel pouch. Cactus Jack’s smiley face logo and Fragment’s signature lightning bolt leave their mark on the left and right heel respectively, as a pre-yellowed midsole supplies Nike Air cushioning underfoot.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 12, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 12, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 12, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2002 Air Jordan 17 OG Low BLACK Black Chrome' CHROME The Heritage Collection'.

node.text:
Michael Jordan rejoined the NBA in the 2001-2002 season and Jordan Brand created an all-new shoe for his return. Referencing his mid-air wizardry, the Air Jordan 17 was inspired by his improvisational nature whenever he took flight and the smooth, sophisticated style of jazz music. 

They came equipped with a large volume Air bag in the heel, achieved through a blow-molded process, a full-length shank plate and a TPU heel stabilizer, making this the most expensive Air Jordan at the time.

The Flight Club Heritage Collection is an explorative series that revisits the past and rediscovers the golden era of sneakers. Shop history now at Flight Club.

node.text: Renewing the collaboration between Converse and the UK-based sneaker boutique, the Offspring x Chuck 70 High 'Paisley Patchwork’ features a vibrant, multi-colored canvas upper with the outsole to match. Red, black, and grey overlays are contrasted by visible stitching throughout the shoe, while a beige rubber outsole provides traction underfoot.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 10, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 10, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 09, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Virgil Abloh merges his signature design system with one of Nike’s most innovative running shoes to create the Off-White x Air Zoom Tempo Next% ‘Black.’ Constructed with a breathable and lightweight knit, the performance runner features a black base with contrasting white accents along the laces and painted-on Swoosh. Scream Green overlays appear throughout the tongue and outsole, the latter equipped with racing-inspired rubber spikes for next-level traction.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 09, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 09, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 08, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: The Wmns Lahar Low 'Wheat' offers a street-ready revamp to the original Lahar Escape Boot – Nike’s vintage hiking shoes from 1989. Seated atop a speckled black midsole equipped with Nike Air cushioning, the sneaker is clad in a tan suede upper with jet black overlays throughout the Swoosh, outsole and utility pull tab located on the heel.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 08, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 08, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 07, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Reminiscent of the Wu-Tang x Dunk High released in 1999 exclusively to Wu-Tang members and their Killa Beez collective, the Air Jordan 1 High Retro OG 'Pollen' brings back the classic silhouette in a familiar two-tone colorway. The high-top sports a premium, black leather upper with titular yellow overlays throughout, giving way to an all-white midsole with Nike Air cushioning underfoot.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 06, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: The 2002R 'Protection Pack - Sea Salt’ revives the classic New Balance silhouette in deconstructed fashion, with textural suede panels tearing apart to reveal the base layer underneath. Featuring a mix of fabrics in Sea Salt and Munsell White, the sneaker boasts a neutral color scheme with sandy, beige overlays atop a NERGY foam midsole. Additionally, rough-cut textures work in tandem with an exposed-foam tongue to finish off the distressed look.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Flight Club on August 06, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 06, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 06, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 05, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Nike’s Doernbecher program launched in 2004, giving patients at the Oregon-based Children's Hospital an opportunity to design their own shoe. The Air Jordan 1 Retro High ‘Doernbecher’ 2008 arrives courtesy of Tony Taylor, a hoops fan from Portland who underwent kidney transplant surgery at the age of 16. Showcasing a vibrant combination of patterns and tropical motifs, the custom sneaker sports a patent leather upper in the Denver Nuggets’ team colors, a nod to Tony’s favorite athlete at the time – Carmelo Anthony. Visible stitching in a Varsity Maize finish adds contrast over a blue gradient skyline, while a personal message on the tongue tag reads ‘I’M FRESH’ in all caps.

Photo by Flight Club on August 05, 2021. May be an image of footwear.
Photo by Flight Club on August 04, 2021. May be an image of footwear and text that says 'COMME des GARÇONS PLUS HOMME'.

node.text: Originally debuted at the fashion label’s Spring/Summer 2021 show in Tokyo, the Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Air Carnivore 'Black' revamps the 1993 trainer in a stealthy, blacked-out aesthetic. The shoe comes equipped with a mesh and synthetic leather upper, high-cut neoprene collar and signature 'Comme des Garçons Homme Plus' branding printed on the heel, while utility straps with 3M reflective detailing complete the sneaker’s technical design.

node.text: Nike and CLOT put the closing seal on their three-part collection with the CLOT x Air Max 1 'Kiss of Death - Solar Red.’ Featuring a redesigned upper and breathable mesh toe box, the sneaker incorporates reflexology and Chinese calligraphy as an homage to its Hong Kong heritage. Nodding to the brand’s storied history, bright pink synthetic suede panels embezzled with signature ‘CLOT’ branding mirror the limited-edition pair given to Kanye West during the 2006 ‘Touch the Sky’ tour in Hong Kong.

node.text: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Ash Blue' presents a re-engineered Primeknit upper, with a slew of blue, grey and black fibers woven throughout. A striking, yellow streak cuts along the lateral side of the shoe, while a semi-translucent rubber midsole transports the full-length Boost unit underneath.

node.text: Accompanying the opening of Virgil Abloh’s exhibit at Boston’s Institute of Contemporary Art, the Off-White x Air Force 1 Low 'Lemonade' dresses the classic silhouette in a vibrant University Gold and Metallic Silver Swoosh. The sneaker features signature Off-White details including exposed stitching, Helvetica text along the medial side and bright orange zip ties looped around the laces.
